            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Now I discovered the following code\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c096561041840826245a82699dfb49064d326c52/src/nvim/buffer.h#L95-L98\r\n\r\nSo it seems possible to detect changes before TextChanged{*} are fired through dictwatcheradd\r\n\r\n```vim\r\n  call dictwatcheradd(b:, \"changedtick\", function(\"OnBufChangedTick\", [buf]))\r\n```\r\n\r\nI *assume* that, whenever a change happens, OnBufChangedTick is called before EVENT_TEXTCHANGED is fired since the latter relies on changedtick, while the dictwatcheradd callbacks are triggered right after changedtick is set on `buffer.c`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/67d3c98dac6a828117f076dcc1a8cc4123024a67/src/nvim/normal.c#L1243-L1245",
